TITLE: Trial set for Black soldier suing police over violent stop
SUMMARY: A U.S. Army lieutenant who was pepper sprayed, struck and handcuffed by police in Virginia but never arrested will argue to a jury next week that he was assaulted and falsely imprisoned and that his vehicle was illegally searched

SUMMARY: The winning numbers were drawn Friday night for the Mega Millions jackpot worth an estimated $940 million. After no winner was declared, the prize surpassed $1.1 billion.

SUMMARY: The FDA has granted accelerated approval to a new Alzheimer's drug.
